ImStack(n_layers=4, base_size=32, scale=2, init_image=None, out_size=256, decay=0.7, device=device(type='cpu')) :: Module

This class represents an image as a series of stacked arrays, where each is 1/2 the resolution of the next. This is useful eg when trying to create an image to minimise some loss - parameters in the early (small) layers can have an affect on the overall structure and shapes while those in later layers act as residuals and fill in fine detail.
